      "span_text": "In Section 2, we introduce the notion of a δ-invariant σ-trace on a left H-category D H (see Definition 2.  , where (δ, σ) is a modular pair in involution for the Hopf algebra H. Given such a trace, we prove (see Theorem 2.4) that there is a characteristic map The pairing in (1.4) suggests that we look for a similar pairing when the Hopf algebra H is replaced by an H-module coalgebra C and the SAYD module σ k δ is replaced by an arbitrary SAYD module M ."
